※※
# ci-autofix

Fires when a CI check run fails on a pull request. Three steps run in sequence:

  fetch   — pulls the failed job log from GitHub using the `gh` CLI
  fix     — Claude diagnoses the failure and applies a code fix (worktree isolation)
  push    — commits the fix and pushes it to the PR branch

Trigger syntax:

  trigger.github.events = ["check_run.completed"]
  trigger.github.check_run.conclusion = "failure"

Only fires for failed checks. `pr.number` is present when GitHub links the
check run to a pull request; the push step guards against missing PRs by
checking the env var before committing.

Available vars: {{check_run.name}}, {{check_run.conclusion}},
{{check_run.html_url}}, {{check_run.head_sha}}, {{pr.number}},
{{repo.full_name}}.
※※

⊕meta⊕
name = "ci-autofix"
description = "Auto-fix a failed CI check run on a PR. Fire via: GitHub check_run.completed webhook with conclusion=failure"
trigger.github.events = ["check_run.completed"]
trigger.github.check_run.conclusion = "failure"
output_style = "terse"
max_budget_usd = 1.00
⊕⊕

※※
Step 1: fetch the failed job log. Uses the gh CLI to retrieve the failed step
output so Claude has the concrete error to work from.
※※

§fetch§
bash = "gh run list --repo \"$SKY_REPO_FULL_NAME\" --commit \"$SKY_CHECK_RUN_HEAD_SHA\" --json databaseId,conclusion --jq '[.[] | select(.conclusion==\"failure\")] | first | .databaseId' > /tmp/sky_run_id.txt 2>&1\nRUN_ID=$(cat /tmp/sky_run_id.txt)\nif [ -z \"$RUN_ID\" ] || [ \"$RUN_ID\" = \"null\" ]; then\n  echo \"[ci-autofix] no failed run found for SHA $SKY_CHECK_RUN_HEAD_SHA\"\n  exit 1\nfi\necho \"[ci-autofix] fetching log for run $RUN_ID\"\ngh run view \"$RUN_ID\" --repo \"$SKY_REPO_FULL_NAME\" --log-failed 2>&1 | head -500"
§§

※※
Step 2: Claude reads the failure log from $SKY_OUTPUT_fetch, diagnoses the
root cause, and applies a fix. Runs in a fresh worktree so changes are isolated.
※※

§fix§
depends_on = ["fetch"]
isolation = "worktree"
model = "sonnet"
max_budget_usd = 0.80
§§

∆fix∆
CI check run "{{check_run.name}}" failed on commit {{check_run.head_sha}} in {{repo.full_name}}. Failed job log:
$SKY_OUTPUT_fetch
From log, diagnose root cause and apply minimal code fix that makes check pass; don't refactor unrelated code; run relevant tests locally to verify if you can. Then output brief summary: what failed, why, what you changed.
∆∆

※※
Step 3: stage, commit, and push the fix to the PR branch. Only runs when
pr.number is set (i.e., the check run is linked to a pull request).
※※

§push§
depends_on = ["fix"]
bash = "if [ -z \"$SKY_PR_NUMBER\" ]; then\n  echo \"[ci-autofix] no PR number — skipping push (branch-only check run)\"\n  exit 0\nfi\ngit add -A\ngit diff --cached --quiet && echo \"[ci-autofix] nothing to commit\" && exit 0\ngit commit -m \"ci: auto-fix from check run $SKY_CHECK_RUN_NAME\"\ngit push"
§§
